What is a Laminar Airflow Cabinet?
Laminar airflow cabinets are specialized air purification systems designed to create sterile, particle-free working environments. These systems utilize High-Efficiency Particulate Air (HEPA) filters to maintain controlled airflow patterns, preventing contamination in sensitive applications. Available in both horizontal and vertical flow configurations, these cabinets are essential components in laboratories, pharmaceutical facilities, and medical institutions where air quality directly impacts research integrity and product safety.

